AIM:
To write a C++ program to implement single inheritance using private and public access
specifiers.
ALGORITHM:
1. Create a base class with one data member and function.
2. Derive a class publicly from the base class.
3. Access base class data using derived class object.
4. Display the result.
PROGRAM:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
class Base {
protected:
int a;
public:
void getData() {
cout << "Enter a value: ";
cin >> a;
}
};
class Derived : public Base {
public:
void display() {
cout << "Value of a = " << a << endl;
}
};
int main() {
Derived obj;
obj.getData();
obj.display();
return 0;
}

Output:
Enter a value: 10
Value of a = 10
